. * -------------------------------------------------------
. * HAUSMAN TEST: FE vs RE
. * -------------------------------------------------------

. estimates store fe_result
. xtreg lnOutput lnLabor lnCapital Leverage lnWage lnSize, re
. estimates store re_result
. hausman fe_result re_result

                  ---- Coefficients ----
              |         (b)           (B)          (b-B)  sqrt(diag(V_b-V_B))
              |   fe_result     re_result     Difference                 S.E.
--------------+------------------------------------------------------------
       lnLabor|   0.5050465     0.6246727     -0.1196262            0.0355267
     lnCapital|   0.0365450     0.0266473      0.0098977            0.0151121
      Leverage|  -0.0179684     0.0256888     -0.0436572            0.0345364
        lnWage|   0.3454143     0.4066738     -0.0612596            0.0243194
        lnSize|   0.2674876     0.4044646     -0.1369769            0.0362796
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

            b = consistent under Ho and Ha; obtained from xtreg
            B = inconsistent under Ha, efficient under Ho; obtained from xtreg

Test:  Ho:  difference in coefficients not systematic

                chi2(5) = (b-B)'[(V_b-V_B)^(-1)](b-B)
                        =      42.00
            Prob>chi2 =      0.0000

  => Reject Ho: Use FIXED EFFECTS model  ***

==============================================================================
. * -------------------------------------------------------
. * DIAGNOSTIC TESTS
. * -------------------------------------------------------

. * [1] Breusch-Pagan / Cook-Weisberg test for heteroscedasticity
. hettest

Breusch-Pagan / Cook-Weisberg test for heteroskedasticity
         Ho: Constant variance
         Variables: fitted values of lnOutput

               chi2(1)      = 424.3034
               Prob > chi2  = 0.0000

  => Reject Ho: Heteroscedasticity detected — use robust SE

. * [2] Durbin-Watson statistic (serial correlation)
. dwstat

Durbin-Watson d-statistic(6, 2294) = 1.21349

  => Positive serial correlation detected

